<h1>Democracy vs. Libertarianism</h1>
15 Aug 93<p>

The one comment I'd make on the wolves vs sheep analogy is this.  In the
real world, there <em>are</em> both wolves and sheep.  Violence and coercion are part
of life.  Democracy, in a sense, recognizes the power implicit in large
numbers of people.  If they can't vote, they may revolt.  No libertarian
government will survive without the acceptance of the masses.</p><p>

A populace willing to countenance a Libertarian society would perhaps be
wise enough to be entrusted with democracy, anyway.</p><p>

</p><address>
Hal Finney<br>
hal@rain.org<br>
</address>
